OL,3,CChinook disaster families call on PM
OL,4,Cto attend meeting
OL,6,FThe crash killed 25 senior
OL,7,Fintelligence experts and four special
OL,8,Fforces crew, when the RAF Chinook
OL,9,FZD576 crashed on the Mull of Kintyre
OL,10,Fen route from RAF Aldergrove in
OL,11,FNorthern Ireland to Fort George near
OL,12,FInverness on 2 June 1994.
OL,14,FThe incident was initially blamed on
OL,15,Fpilot error before being overturned in
OL,16,F2011. The two pilots, Richard Cook and
OL,17,FJonathan Tapper were based at RAF
OL,18,FOdiham in Hampshire.
